SIMPLE: waterproof
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waterproof
<hw>Wa"ter*proof`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Proof against
penetration or permeation by water; impervious to water; <as>as, a
<ex>waterproof</ex> garment; a <ex>waterproof</ex> roof</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waterproof</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Waterproof
<hw>Wa"ter*proof`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A substance or
preparation for rendering cloth, leather, etc., impervious to
water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Cloth made waterproof, or any article made of such
cloth, or of other waterproof material, as rubber; esp., an outer
garment made of such material.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waterproof</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Waterproof
<hw>Wa"ter*proof`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To render
impervious to water, as cloth, leather, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waterproofing</ent>⟦br⟧
